description: {"blocks":[{"key":"ca9so","text":"Paraffin sections (4 μm thickness) of formalin-fixed human pancreases and isolated human islets were treated with 0.05% pronase for antigen retrieval. HS and Col18 HSPG core proteins were detected immunohistochemically using 10E4 anti-HS (US Biological/Amsbio) and anti-Col18 (Santa Cruz), respectively, with horseradish peroxidase-conjugated rabbit anti-mouse Ig (Dako). Background staining was checked using the corresponding isotype control Ig instead of the primary antibody. 3-amino-9-ethylcarbazole (AEC) was used as the chromogen. For morphometry, stained sections were imaged using a light microscope with attached camera (Olympus BX41). Image J software with color deconvolution plugin was used for the quantitative analysis of the % of islet area stained","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"20oe","text":"10E4 anti-heparan sulfate (HS) mAb identifies highly sulfated HS localised in human beta cells but does not identify the less sulfated HS in alpha cells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"endha","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"aa18r","text":"Reference:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"c0aqt","text":"Theodoraki A, Hu Y, Poopalasundaram S et al (2015) Mol Cell Endocrinol 399: 296-310.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1nbt6","text":"Deparaffinize slides in each xylene for 1 min. rehydrate slides in graded alcohols beginning in absolute ethanol (10 dips)/ container of absolute ethanol), followed by 90% ethanol (10 dips) and 70% ethanol (10 dips). Wash well in running tap water for 5 min. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7rc1a","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"670us","text":"Wipe around sections with a tissue, encircle the sections using a diamond pencil and place in a slide container of tap water (250 ml). {"blocks":[{"key":"8n9rk","text":"Block endogenous peroxidase activity by incubating sections in 3% hydrogen peroxide in methanol (25 ml 30% H2O2 + 225 ml methanol) for 10 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":108,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":110,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"38eng","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6bra7","text":"Wash 2 x 2 min in 250 ml phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) followed by wash in running tap water for 5 min.
